programme.title: Most Haunted: Commissioner's House and Dock Yard
programme.desc: Many ghosts are said to haunt the Commissioner's House and dockyard. As the crew investigates, Yvette is frozen in sheer terror, Derek is possessed by an evil spirit and Karl braves the dark alone.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Guildhall
programme.desc: Guildhall in Leicester was once a court house, a police headquarters and a school. Loud, inexplicable footsteps are caught on camera and the crew becomes ill while in a cell.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Greengate Brewery
programme.desc: J.W. Lees & Co. brewery is still going strong after more than 175 years in business. When the team visits, Derek discovers several spirits. Who is tapping and rolling the barrels?

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Manor House Restaurant
programme.desc: The Manor House was redeveloped, forgotten and rediscovered in the 1950s. While investigating, the crew is terrified by a room that was sealed off and has caused paranormal mayhem since reopening.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Chough Hotel, Chard, Somerset
programme.desc: Witchcraft, ghostly apparitions and mysterious footsteps keep the team on their toes in Somerset. Presenter Dr. David Bull braves a lone vigil in the attic, a decision he will live to regret.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Old Hall Hotel, Sandbach, Cheshire
programme.desc: Television presenter and avid "Most Haunted" viewer Gaby Roslin joins the team in Cheshire. As events escalate, a curious combination of baths, bees and books ensures a far from pleasant stay.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Child of God
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark are on hand when a dying woman attempts a reconciliation with her estranged father. She is a single mother who wants her family to take the child.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Match Made in Heaven
programme.desc: Scotty is a lovelorn quadriplegic with a successful law practice. Jonathan is happy to play cupid, but Mark isn't so thrilled about it, because the woman in question is his cousin.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Banker and The Bum
programme.desc: A greedy banker and a good-hearted bum switch places. The bum dies, but the banker is now infused with love and generosity.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Brightest Star
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark meet a child star whose fame is spoiling her rotten, destroying her family and taking away her childhood.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Investment In Caring
programme.desc: Jonathan encourages residents in a neighborhood to unite against a cold-hearted developer.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Right Thing
programme.desc: Jonathan inspires a young man to help the grandfather who has recently been placed in a nursing home.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Thoroughbreds - Part 1
programme.desc: Lizzy MacGill is a horse trainer's young daughter who elopes with Garth Armstrong, a privileged man.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Spinning a More Youthful Look
programme.desc: Evan is a mobile DJ who is trying to take his business to the next level. Evan hasn't had the time or money to take care his looks but he knows it's absolutely necessary now if his business is going to continue growing.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Getting Back on the Catwalk
programme.desc: Stacey is a former model whose appearance has gone downhill because of the demands of caring for both her new baby and her ill mother. She's eager to get back on the catwalk and our team of experts will do a head to toe transformation.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Ronnie Donno
programme.desc: Teaching assistant Ronnie Donno already feels bad about the way she looks but before work can begin on getting her to look younger she has to hear how old 100 members of the public think she looks.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Jackie Ralph
programme.desc: Inside, Jackie Ralph still feels like a flirty young woman. Only problem is, she's trapped inside the body of a 61 year old – at least that's what the British public think. Nicky Hambleton Jones and her team of experts take charge.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Beauty is More Than Skin Deep
programme.desc: Tracy is a dedicated single mom, and a survivor. After devastating cystic acne scarred her face, she suffered a terrible oven accident that left her with even more scars. Our team of experts, and The Glam Squad, give Tracy the TLC she deserves
programme.sub-title: Beauty is More Than Skin Deep

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Polishing the Prize
programme.desc: Ellisa is a recent newlywed whose life hasn't felt much like a honeymoon since her husband is always on the road for work and she is left at home with a new baby! Fearing that her husband could stray while away, our team of experts help Ellisa.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand
programme.desc: Everyone wants to look younger but if you work hard and play hard like Sue Whyte, it's far tougher to roll back those years. Sue's already stopped smoking and lost a lot of weight so can Fiona McDonald and her team of time warriors take care of the rest?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: No Pain No Gain
programme.desc: Once a sun-worshipping fashion model, Linda led a charmed life of good looks. After the devastating loss of her family, life became difficult. Linda is willing to do anything to recover her former looks and finds out that beauty comes with a price.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Homecoming Queen Gets Her Crown Back
programme.desc: In her youth, Catherine was a wild child punk rocker whose bright red mohawk got her elected homecoming queen. But now that Catherine is a single mother of twin teenage daughters, she feels like she's lost her young, eye-catching style.
programme.sub-title: The Homecoming Queen Gets Her Crown Back

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Guilty Of Needing A Makeover
programme.desc: After a career as a cop and a private investigator, Lita worked her way through law school while raising her son. She's finished school and taken the bar exam, but her face and body have paid the price.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Prepping For The Big Day
programme.desc: Lilia is the first in her family to finish college. She helps support her family and bought a house she shares with her mother. Her achievements have carried a price; she looks old and tired compared to her friends.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A New Look On Life
programme.desc: At one time Trisha was a golden locked, free-spirited surfer, but once she settled down and had children her looks and self-esteem took a downward spiral. Suddenly single again, Trisha needs help searching for her energetic youth.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Out of Hiding
programme.desc: Tammy has lost over 100 pounds, but says she feels like she actually looks older! After years of hiding under oversized clothes and bulky glasses, she doesn't know how to dress and take care of her new body.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Debbie Rotchell
programme.desc: Essex girl Debbie Rotchell, 49, smokes 15,000 cigarettes a year and loves to sunbathe. Debbie gets a wake-up call when a poll of one hundred people puts her at 55. Just as well Nicky Hambleton-Jones is on hand with her time-fighting trio.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Everyone's excited at the prospect of Leopard's Den's new arrival. Bash, Danny's old tutor and Rosie's Godfather, is coming from England to help Danny grow his veterinary practice.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: The Trevanions are delighted when Fatani asks Danny to take an aggressive hippo off his hands. As they prepare for its arrival Sarah gets a bit of a shock when her mother Caroline beats the hippo to the post.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Business is looking up at Leopard's Den but Sarah is feeling agitated. Caroline thinks it because Simon, her ex husband and Evan and Olivia's Dad, is arriving from England to get married. But Sarah has other things on her mind.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny is undertaking a drugs trial at Leopard's Den. But de-worming wildebeest isn't Caroline's idea of fun. She hates animals and finds the whole business mind-numbingly boring.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Du Plessis is in a foul mood. It's his 60th birthday and he has no intentions of celebrating it. But the Trevanions have other ideas and Caroline is organising a surprise party.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: All is quiet at Leopard's Den as Sarah, Evan and Olivia gather at the hospital. Danny has been given the all clear to go home. But Du Plessis is still unconscious and seriously ill. Caroline keeps a tender vigil at his bedside.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: New lodges nearly break the family, but they learn that it's the animals which make Leopard's Den a success.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10
programme.desc: A motocross rider may have broken his back after hitting a tree head on at high speed, at a sawmill a man faces its worse nightmares; and a woman is fighting for her life after taking an accidental overdose of her husband's medication.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: Auckland's Westpac helicopter crew races to save two teenage girls fighting for their lives after their car crashed and rolled the Waiwera Hill.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2
programme.desc: Professional scuba diver Brian Green has been found floating and not breathing, and is on a boat near the Noises, a group of islands in the Hauraki Gulf. The team has to move fast.

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 1
programme.desc: Pig farmer Keith and graphic designer Jonathon are about to take on the toughest job of their lives. Their worn-out wives Rosh and Natalie have gone on strike and are spending three days at a luxury spa.

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 2
programme.desc: Telecoms Consultant Daren and Quantity Surveyor Tony are about to take on the toughest job of their lives. Their hard-working wives Astra and Justine have gone on strike.

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 3
programme.desc: Salesman Abdul and muscle man Martin are about to take on the toughest job of their lives. Their wives Zeena and Nicola have gone on strike and are spending three days at a luxury spa.

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 4
programme.desc: House of Lords Chef, Graham and car salesman, Lee are about to take on the toughest job of their lives. Their worn-out wives Lisa and Claudia have gone on strike and are spending three days at a spa.

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 5
programme.desc: Bus driver Tom and forklift truck driver Darren take on the toughest job of their lives. Their worn-out wives Michelle and Claire have gone on strike and are spending three days at a spa.

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 6
programme.desc: Builder Glenn and body-builder Chris are about to take on the toughest job of their lives. Their worn-out wives Lisa and Dawn have gone on strike and are spending three days at a luxury spa.

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 7
programme.desc: Lorry driver Paul, and Businessman, Alex are about to take on the toughest job of their lives. Their worn-out wives, Julia and Eiko have gone on strike and are spending three days at a luxury spa.

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 8
programme.desc: Electrician Andrew and corporate-whizz Mathew are about to take on the toughest job of their lives. Their worn-out wives Natasha and Anna have gone on strike and are spending 3 days at a luxury spa.

programme.title: 4x4: Extraordinary SUVs
programme.desc: This Mitsubishi Outlander Plug-In Hybrid is the world's first hybrid SUV with two electric motors and a 2-liter combustion engine. We tested if such a combination makes sense for offroad vehicles. Also: the Chevrolet Silverado...

programme.title: 4x4: SUV Girlpower
programme.desc: Nancy and Nadia, two daring Jordanian women faced the challenge to cross the Moroccan desert in a Hummer H3. The two professional racers took part in the Conti 4x4 Trophy - a demanding rally through the Atlas Mountains and the Western Sahara.

programme.title: 4x4: SUV Concepts
programme.desc: Before Bentley and Jaguar started producing their own luxury SUV models, the two British brands presented their take on this special range of cars. We took a look at their concept cars, the Bentley EXP 9F and Jaguar's C-X17.

programme.title: 4x4: Normal vs. Lifestyle SUVs
programme.desc: The SUVs Nissan X-Trail and BMW X4 certainly aren't typical offroaders. We witnessed Nissan's presentation of their new X-Trail model and the BMW X4 world premiere in Bilbao. Also: the Steinbeißer Trophy...

programme.title: 4x4: American SUVs
programme.desc: In the United States, SUVs aren't usually considered simple workhorses but rather treated as regular everyday vehicles. US-Americans don't want to miss out on space, comfort and loading capacity. Their motto is: the bigger, the better.

programme.title: 4x4: Tuned SUVs
programme.desc: SUVs usually are rather impressive right out of the factory, but there are many tuning and customizing options: huge wheels, crazy colors and perfomance similar to super sports cars. One might ask if such alterations are really necessary, but enthusi…

programme.title: 4x4: Small, strong, stylish
programme.desc: At first glance, compact cars like the Audi A1, the Volkswagen Golf and the Mini don't seem to belong in this series, but when the "A1" becomes the "S1" and the Golf gets a "R" in its name, these small cars turn into all-wheel beasts.

programme.title: 4x4: Fascination offroad
programme.desc: At the All-Wheel Adventure in Bad Kissingen, Germany, the biggest exhibition for offroaders in Europe, we test drove the Rallye Defender and examined how a regular Jeep Wrangler with only a few modifications could double in price.

programme.title: 4x4: All- Wheel- Drive on snow
programme.desc: In winter, when the streets get slippery, an all-wheel drive vehicle brings many advantages as you gain more traction. Under icy conditions we experienced one day in snowy Austria with rally professional Niki Schelle in a Suzuki SX4 S-Cross.

programme.title: 4x4: Rallye Fun
programme.desc: Countryside tours aren't the only option with an all-wheel drive car. You can also have a lot of fun on gravel roads. We show how that goes in a Subaru WRX STI. Also: in the 1990s, Ford had a successful go at international rally competitions...

programme.title: 4x4: All- Wheel- Drive on station wagons
programme.desc: Station wagons are usually regarded as family cars or just vehicles with a lot of cargo hold. But the Skoda Octavia, the Opel Insignia Country Tourer, the Subaru Outback, the Audi S4 allroad quattro and the Seat Leon x-perience want to be more than...
programme.sub-title: All- Wheel- Drive on station wagons

programme.title: 4x4: Extreme offroad cars
programme.desc: In this episode, we take a look at some of the more extreme specimens in the offroad world: a Fiat Panda monster truck whose tires have a diameter of 1.5 meters, a Ford Raptor with 600 hp, a conversion of a Mercedes G-class Edition by ORC...

programme.title: Biker Lifestyle: Across Utah on a Harley 2011, Part 1
programme.desc: Utah, land of red rocks. That is what is was called by the original inhabitants. Hardly anywhere else on earth are there so many natural wonders in such a small area. And we want to experience this extraordinary nature. (Part 1 of 4)
programme.sub-title: Across Utah on a Harley 2011, Part 1

programme.desc: A group posing as volunteers attacks using a stolen skrill prototype that does not require an implant to control. It is discovered that the skrill queen is also missing. The investigation leads to a resistance group called Black Wednesday.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Déjà Vu
programme.desc: A joint Doors International/Taelon venture creates a machine that allows people to vividly relive a memory, but Liam suspects a back alley version of the device is leading to the death of some users.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Once and Future World

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Arrival

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Forge of Creation

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: First Breath
programme.desc: A college friend of Renee's resurfaces and leads them on an investigation of the link between the Taelons and a biomedical facility's cloning operation.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Sins of the Father
programme.desc: A Senator's daughter is found to have kryss in her system. Liam and Renee suspect the Taelons lied about synthesizing it and there is a new location for production. They believe Federov is involved. Da'an is addicted to kryss.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Phantom Companion
programme.desc: While on board the mothership, Renee sustains an injury and while being treated, she gets pulled into the walls and disappears.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Dream Stalker
programme.desc: Street asks Liam to help a friend who's arrested for the murder of a man he hated. Liam talks to him and he claims that he dreamed of killing him.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Lost Generation
programme.desc: A CVI malfunctions and kills a soon-to-be father. The investigation leads Liam and Renee to a fertility clinic. Renee finds out she is infertile and suspects that Taelon technology is affecting worldwide fertility.
